properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 6 at 10:35AM MST until January 6 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Denver CO
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow. Additional snow accumulation less
than 2 inches. Winds gusts from 60 to 70 mph above timberline
and exposed eastern slopes.

* WHERE...The Mountains of Summit County, the Mosquito Range,
and the Indian Peaks and Rocky Mountain National Park and the
Medicine Bow Range.

* WHEN...Until 5 PM MST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Blowing snow could
significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous conditions could
impact the evening commute. Strong winds could cause tree
damage. The cold wind chills as low as 25 below zero could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON
